diff:1670580386:1670561519:=77,91d76%0a%3c #foxbegin 221209-100626-452240#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Similarities between the Milan Conference and classical Oppression %0a%3c -> - haridesikan%0a%3c -> [-09.12.2022 - 02:06-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221209-100626-452240 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c In some sense, the Milan Conference was a manner of oppression not so different from so many others; it attempted to save face by "looking towards the education of deaf children" and came up with "strategies to teach the deaf via the spoken word." We see this happen in many oppressive scenarios (I shan't name examples as they are too numerous to count); the tale is spun as "helping" the oppressed out by including some blanket bullet points, but really seeks to do nothing than to advance the goal of the oppressors. Sign language, however, survived long enough to be restored to some level; much like the stories we do hear of failed attempts at oppression, there is light at the end of this story.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221209-100626-452240#%0a
